{
  "texts": [
    "It is important to note that Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks differ from DoS attacks in terms of their origin.",
    "DoS attacks stem from a solitary system, while DDoS attacks are executed through multiple systems, rendering them swifter and more difficult to obstruct.",
    "Phishing is a type of cyberattack that employs various methods such as email, SMS, phone calls, social media, and social engineering techniques to deceive victims into sharing sensitive information like passwords or account numbers.",
    "Attackers may also trick victims into downloading malicious files, which could install viruses on their computers or phones.",
    "Other types of cyber security attacks include Spoofing, Identity-based attacks, Code injection attacks, and supply chain attacks, among others.These examples highlight the diverse and evolving nature of cyber threats, necessitating constant vigilance and the adoption of advanced security measures to safeguard against them."
  ]
}